    "developed a CNN model that could detect and localize microaneurysms with a sensitivity of 96.5% and a false positive rate of 0.3 per image.",
    "This demonstrates the potential of AI not just to detect disease but also to provide a detailed analysis of retinal pathology, enlightening us about the capabilities of AI in ophthalmology (12).",
    "The integration of AI into clinical workflows for DR screening has also been explored.",
    "teleophthalmology program, achieving a sensitivity of 91.0% and a specificity of 95.4% for detecting referable DR (13).",
    "The model's performance was comparable to that of human graders, suggesting that AI could be effectively incorporated into existing teleophthalmology systems to enhance DR screening efficiency and accessibility."
